TY  - JOUR
AU  - Foucault, Thierry
AU  - Frésard, Laurent
T1  - Cross-Listing, Investment Sensitivity to Stock Price, and the Learning Hypothesis
PY  - 2012
Y1  - 2012/11/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhs093
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 25
IS  - 11
SP  - 3305
EP  - 3350
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - Cross-listed firms in the United States have a higher investment-to-price sensitivity than do firms that never cross-list. This difference is strong, does not exist prior to the cross-listing date, and does not vanish afterward. Moreover, it does not appear to be primarily driven by improvements in governance, disclosure, and access to capital associated with a U.S. cross-listing. Instead, we argue that a cross-listing enhances managers' reliance on stock prices because it makes stock prices more informative to them. Consistent with this explanation, U.S. cross-listings that are more likely to strengthen the informativeness of stock prices for managers feature a higher investment-to-price sensitivity.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhs093
ER  - 



